  "title": "Procurement Specialist APAC",
  "description": "<p><strong>Your role</strong></p><p>This junior role is ideal for candidates with a strong foundation in procurement processes and a passion for supporting business operations. The Procurement Specialist will assist in day-to-day procurement activities including purchase order (PO) issuance, supplier onboarding, tender coordination, and general administrative support.</p><p><strong>What you’ll do</strong></p><p>•\tIssue and manage purchase orders in accordance with company policies and procedures</p><p>•\tSupport supplier onboarding and maintain accurate supplier records</p><p>•\tAssist in tender preparation, coordination, and documentation</p><p>•\tLiaise with internal stakeholders to gather procurement requirements</p><p>•\tTrack and follow up on order deliveries and resolve basic supply issues</p><p>•\tMaintain procurement documentation and ensure compliance with audit requirements</p><p>•\tSupport data entry and reporting for procurement metrics and KPIs</p><p>•\tContribute to continuous improvement initiatives within the procurement function</p><p><strong>What you’ll need</strong></p><p>•\tBachelor’s degree/diploma in Business Administration, Supply Chain Management, or a related field</p><p>•\tMinimum 1 year of relevant work experience in procurement or supply chain</p><p>•\tFamiliarity with procurement systems (e.g., Yardi, SAP, Oracle) is a plus</p><p>•\tStrong organizational and communication skills</p><p>•\tDetail-oriented with the ability to manage multiple tasks</p><p>•\tProficient in Microsoft Office Suite (Excel, Word, PowerPoint)</p>",
